abstract: >
  A comprehensive guide to designing scalable and resilient web applications.
  This book covers fundamental concepts of distributed systems, architectural
  patterns, scalability strategies, database design, caching, security, and
  system design best practices. Topics include CAP theorem, SOLID principles,
  load balancing, consistent hashing, message queues, and capacity estimation.
